<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-21T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-21T05:00:00-05:00" n="901" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d901">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">867.248 Martin Co., Glenn L./18:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-21T12:00:00+02:00">February 21, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:40
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5. Prime Minister requests me to state Turkish Government has
                                arranged to buy 16 Martin bombers in the United States.
                                Manufacturers are producing four bombers monthly but on account of
                                War Department orders cannot undertake to deliver more than one
                                monthly to Turkey beginning next year. Prime Minister expresses
                                urgent hope that American Government will authorize manufacturers to
                                deliver two bombers monthly to Turkey beginning in August. Knowing
                                as I do that Turkish Government extremely anxious to obtain these
                                deliveries I trust Department may be able to obtain prompt and
                                favorable decision.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>